                        <p class=" text-justify ">Information technology (IT) is the use of computers to store, retrieve, transmit, and manipulate
                                data, or information, often in the context of a business or other enterprise. IT is considered
                                to be a subset of information and communications technology (ICT). The term is commonly used
                                as a synonym for computers and computer networks, but it also encompasses other information
                                distribution technologies such as television and telephones. Several products or services
                                within an economy are associated with information technology.</p>
